# Dev server — manual control only

The user starts and stops the Next.js dev server themselves. Do not auto-start it.

## Never do this

- Do not run `npm run dev`, `next dev`, or any variant (including background shells with `block_until_ms: 0`).
- Do not restart the dev server after the user kills it.
- Do not start a dev server to "verify" UI changes, reproduce bugs, or run browser tests unless the user explicitly asks in that message.

## What to do instead

- Use `npm run build` for compile/type verification.
- Use `npm run test` for unit tests.
- If a running server is required and the user has not started one, ask them to run `npm run dev` in their terminal, or use production mode (`npm run build && npm run start`) only when they explicitly request it.

## Manual start (user only)

```bash
npm run dev
```

Runs on http://localhost:4000
